  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6174975 2022-11-30T00:10:59.068726784Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script scripts/GMXHistoricalJSON.s.sol\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI've written a script which is collecting the historical data from the avalanche blockchain by using fork block and roll block. In my specific case script fails with error of running out of gas for tests (but this is a script).\r\n\r\nI've tried to increase the gas value in config but seems like the value in example is maximum value\r\n```\r\ngas_limit = 9223372036854775807\r\n```\r\nSo if I try to increase this value, foundry fails to start because of error in config.",
